[{"location":"api/#API-References","page":"API","title":"API References","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"Modules = [Kitab]","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Kitab.MetaData","page":"API","title":"Kitab.MetaData","text":"MetaData(author, ...)\n\nInstantiate MetaData object\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#Kitab.OpenITIDB","page":"API","title":"Kitab.OpenITIDB","text":"OpenITIDB(url::String)\n\nInstantiate OpenITIDB type using url as input.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#Kitab.OpenITIDB-Tuple{Array{String}}","page":"API","title":"Kitab.OpenITIDB","text":"OpenITIDB(urls::Array{String})\n\nInstantiate OpenITIDB type using multiple urls as input.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#Base.delete!-Tuple{Type{OpenITIDB}}","page":"API","title":"Base.delete!","text":"delete!(::Type{OpenITIDB})\n\nDelete the db folder for saving the downloaded OpenITIDB text\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#Base.download-Tuple{Array{OpenITIDB}}","page":"API","title":"Base.download","text":"download(openitis::Array{OpenITIDB})\n\nDownload OpenITIDB data using an array of it to downloaded multiple data.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#Base.download-Tuple{OpenITIDB}","page":"API","title":"Base.download","text":"download(openiti::OpenITIDB)\n\nDownload the OpenITI data.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#Kitab.extract-Tuple{Type{MetaData}, Array{String}}","page":"API","title":"Kitab.extract","text":"extract(::Type{MetaData}, data::Array{String})\n\nExtract metadata from raw data text.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#Kitab.list-Tuple{Type{OpenITIDB}}","page":"API","title":"Kitab.list","text":"list(::Type{OpenITIDB})\n\nList all the downloaded OpenITI data\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#Kitab.load-Tuple{Type{OpenITIDB}, Int64}","page":"API","title":"Kitab.load","text":"load(::Type{OpenITIDB}, row::Int64)\n\nLoad the downloaded OpenITI data by specifying the row of the file in the output of list(OpenITIDB).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"usage/#Usage","page":"Usage","title":"Usage","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"usage/","page":"Usage","title":"Usage","text":"In this section, we are going to demonstrate how to use the package.","category":"page"},{"location":"usage/#Downloading-OpenITI-Data","page":"Usage","title":"Downloading OpenITI Data","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"usage/","page":"Usage","title":"Usage","text":"The data is available in the repositories of OpenITI Github group, arranged according to Hijrah year of the books. Further, most of these books are also available in the catalog of books metada of the KITAB project, which can be accessed via this link.","category":"page"},{"location":"usage/","page":"Usage","title":"Usage","text":"using Kitab\n\nmuslim_sahih = \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/OpenITI/0275AH/master/data/0261Muslim/0261Muslim.Sahih/0261Muslim.Sahih.Shamela0001727-ara1.mARkdown\";\ndownload(OpenITIDB(muslim_sahih))","category":"page"},{"location":"usage/#Downloading-Multiple-URLs","page":"Usage","title":"Downloading Multiple URLs","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"usage/","page":"Usage","title":"Usage","text":"To download multiple URLs, use an array of it.","category":"page"},{"location":"usage/","page":"Usage","title":"Usage","text":"bukhari_sahih = \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/OpenITI/0275AH/master/data/0256Bukhari/0256Bukhari.Sahih/0256Bukhari.Sahih.JK000110-ara1.completed\"\nbukhari_ducafa = \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/OpenITI/0275AH/master/data/0256Bukhari/0256Bukhari.Ducafa/0256Bukhari.Ducafa.Shamela0008632-ara1.mARkdown\"\n\ndownload(OpenITIDB([bukhari_sahih, bukhari_ducafa]))","category":"page"},{"location":"usage/","page":"Usage","title":"Usage","text":"Once downloaded, re-downloading will not proceed if the file already exists.","category":"page"},{"location":"usage/","page":"Usage","title":"Usage","text":"download(OpenITIDB([bukhari_sahih, bukhari_ducafa]))","category":"page"},{"location":"usage/#List-downloaded-OpenITI-Data","page":"Usage","title":"List downloaded OpenITI Data","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"usage/","page":"Usage","title":"Usage","text":"To list the downloaded data, simply use the list function as follows:","category":"page"},{"location":"usage/","page":"Usage","title":"Usage","text":"list(OpenITIDB)","category":"page"},{"location":"usage/#Load-OpenITI-Data","page":"Usage","title":"Load OpenITI Data","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"usage/","page":"Usage","title":"Usage","text":"To load the data from the list of downloaded OpenITI data, we simply specify the row of the file from the list(OpenITIDB).","category":"page"},{"location":"usage/","page":"Usage","title":"Usage","text":"load(OpenITIDB, 1)\nload(OpenITIDB, 2)\nload(OpenITIDB, 3)","category":"page"},{"location":"usage/#Delete-OpenITI-Local-DB-folder","page":"Usage","title":"Delete OpenITI Local DB folder","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"usage/","page":"Usage","title":"Usage","text":"To delete local DB folder, simply run the following:","category":"page"},{"location":"usage/","page":"Usage","title":"Usage","text":"delete!(OpenITIDB)","category":"page"},{"location":"#Kitab.jl","page":"Home","title":"Kitab.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Kitab.jl is an interface to the Open Islamic Texts Initiative (OpenITI) data. The OpenITI is a multi-institutional effort led by researchers at the Aga Khan University’s Institute for the Study of Muslim Civilisations in London, Roshan Institute for Persian Studies at the University of Maryland, College Park, and Universität Hamburg that aims to develop the digital infrastructure for the study of Islamicate cultures. It provides APIs for downloading, listing, and loading the text data.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Kitab (کتاب) /kitāb/ is the Arabic word for \"book.\" The logo is a Kufic calligraphy of the Arabic word کتاب.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Installation","page":"Home","title":"Installation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"To install the package, run the following:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"julia> using Pkg\njulia> Pkg.add(\"Kitab\")","category":"page"},{"location":"#Outline","page":"Home","title":"Outline","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Pages = [\n    \"usage.md\",\n    \"api.md\"\n]\nDepth = 2","category":"page"}]
